                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/230.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-13T13:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1915—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1638. I received following answer yesterday, in a conversation with Sir Edward
                    Grey, to your 1060 about China.</p>
                <p>“The British Government has made inquiries of Japan but so far has made no
                    comment.”</p>
                <p>Grey showed me telegram from Spring Rice saying that you had informed him of
                    satisfactory interview with Japanese Ambassador in Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador.</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
